---
import SAGPLayout from "../layouts/SAGPLayout.astro";
---

<SAGPLayout title="Society for Ancient Greek Philosophy">

<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="kicker">Welcome</div>
    <h1>Society for Ancient Greek Philosophy</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      A worldwide scholarly conversation since 1953.
    </p>
    <p class="lede">
      SAGP brings together scholars and students devoted to the study of Ancient
      Greek philosophy through conferences, lectures, works in progress, and an
      international community of inquiry.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section">
  <h2>What SAGP does</h2>

  <div class="card-grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h3>Annual Conference</h3>
      <p>
        A yearly gathering for original research, thematic sessions, and
        moderated scholarly discussion.
      </p>
      <p><a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/events/annual-conference/`}>Learn more</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Distinguished Lectureship</h3>
      <p>
        An annual recognition of scholars whose work has made substantial
        contributions to Ancient Greek philosophy.
      </p>
      <p><a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/events/distinguished-lectureship/`}>Explore lectures</a></p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h3>Works in Progress</h3>
      <p>
        A setting for developing ideas through feedback, mentorship, and
        intellectual generosity.
      </p>
      <p><a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/events/works-in-progress/`}>View series</a></p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div>
    <h2>Who we are</h2>
  </div>

  <div>
    <p>
      Founded in 1953, the Society for Ancient Greek Philosophy is an
      international community of scholars and students committed to rigorous
      inquiry, conversation across traditions, and the continuing relevance of
      Ancient Greek philosophy.
    </p>

    <p>
      The Society especially encourages junior and mid-career scholars and seeks
      to sustain a welcoming, diverse, and intellectually generous community.
    </p>

    <p>
      <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/who-we-are/`}>Read more about the Society</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div>
    <h2>Next event</h2>
  </div>

  <div>
    <h3>Annual Conference 2025</h3>
    <p class="muted">
      November 15–16, 2025 · via Zoom · All times listed in Pacific Standard Time.
    </p>
    <p>
      The 2025 SAGP Annual Conference includes sessions on Plato, Aristotle,
      Presocratic ontology, and Stoic epistemology.
    </p>
    <p>
      <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/events/annual-conference/2025/`}>View the conference program</a>
    </p>

    <div class="callout">
      Future enhancement: generate this block automatically from structured
      event data so the homepage always points to the next upcoming SAGP event.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section two-col">
  <div>
    <h2>Become part of the conversation</h2>
  </div>

  <div>
    <p>
      Membership is open to scholars and students of Ancient Greek philosophy.
      Members support the Society’s events, scholarly community, and continuing
      work.
    </p>

    <p>
      <a href={`${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/membership/`}>Learn about membership</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

</SAGPLayout>
